**Custom Redis configuration with JSON serialization:**
```java
import org.springframework.cache.annotation.EnableCaching;
import org.springframework.context.annotation.Bean;
import org.springframework.context.annotation.Configuration;
import org.springframework.data.redis.cache.RedisCacheConfiguration;
import org.springframework.data.redis.serializer.*;
import java.time.Duration;

@Configuration
@EnableCaching
public class CacheConfig {

    @Bean
    public RedisCacheConfiguration cacheConfiguration() {
        return RedisCacheConfiguration.defaultCacheConfig()
            .entryTtl(Duration.ofMinutes(10))  // default TTL
            .disableCachingNullValues()         // don't cache null results
            .serializeValuesWith(
                RedisSerializationContext.SerializationPair.fromSerializer(
                    new GenericJackson2JsonRedisSerializer()  // store as JSON
                )
            );
    }
}
```

concept_explanation.cacheable_annotations:
**The three cache annotations:**

```java
@Service
public class RestaurantService {
    private final RestaurantRepository repo;

    // @Cacheable — read cache; call method only on cache miss:
    @Cacheable(
        value = "restaurants",     // cache name (Redis key prefix)
        key   = "#city",           // cache key (SpEL expression)
        unless = "#result.isEmpty()"  // don't cache empty lists
    )
    public List<Restaurant> getByCity(String city) {
        return repo.findByCityAndActiveTrue(city);
        // Cache miss:  fires, result stored as 'restaurants::Hyderabad'
        // Cache hit:   method NOT called, returns from Redis
    }

    // @CachePut — always call method AND update cache:
    @CachePut(
        value = "restaurants",
        key   = "#result.id"       // key from return value
    )
    public Restaurant save(Restaurant r) {
        return repo.save(r);
        // Always saves to DB; always updates Redis entry
        // Use to keep cache fresh after writes
    }

    // @CacheEvict — remove from cache:
    @CacheEvict(
        value = "restaurants",
        key   = "#city"            // evict specific city
    )
    public void refreshCity(String city) {
        // Next call to getByCity(city) will be a cache miss → fresh DB read
    }

    // @CacheEvict allEntries — clear entire cache:
    @CacheEvict(value = "restaurants", allEntries = true)
    public void clearAll() {
        // Removes ALL entries from the 'restaurants' cache
        // Use after bulk updates
    }
}

// Cache key SpEL examples:
// key = "#id"                     → simple parameter
// key = "#user.id"                → nested field
// key = "'product:' + #productId" → constant prefix
// key = "#root.methodName + #id"  → method name + param
// key = "T(java.util.Objects).hash(#city, #category)" → composite
```

concept_explanation.ttl_and_redis_keys:
**TTL (Time-To-Live) and Redis key patterns:**

```java
// Per-cache TTL with custom configuration:
@Bean
public RedisCacheManager cacheManager(RedisConnectionFactory factory) {
    Map<String, RedisCacheConfiguration> configs = new HashMap<>();

    // Short TTL for fast-changing data:
    configs.put("stock-prices",
        RedisCacheConfiguration.defaultCacheConfig()
            .entryTtl(Duration.ofSeconds(30)));  // 30s: stock prices change fast!

    // Longer TTL for stable data:
    configs.put("restaurants",
        RedisCacheConfiguration.defaultCacheConfig()
            .entryTtl(Duration.ofMinutes(10)));  // 10 min: restaurants don't move

    // Very long TTL for almost-static data:
    configs.put("cities",
        RedisCacheConfiguration.defaultCacheConfig()
            .entryTtl(Duration.ofHours(24)));    // 24h: city list changes rarely

    return RedisCacheManager.builder(factory)
        .cacheDefaults(RedisCacheConfiguration.defaultCacheConfig()
            .entryTtl(Duration.ofMinutes(5)))    // default: 5 minutes
        .withInitialCacheConfigurations(configs)
        .build();
}

// Redis key format (Spring Cache default):
// '{cacheName}::{key}'
// 'restaurants::Hyderabad'  → List<Restaurant> for Hyderabad
// 'restaurants::Mumbai'     → List<Restaurant> for Mumbai
// 'stock-prices::TCS'       → price for TCS

// Verify in redis-cli:
// > KEYS restaurants::*         ← list all restaurant cache entries
// > GET restaurants::Hyderabad  ← view the JSON
// > TTL restaurants::Hyderabad  ← seconds until expiry
// > DEL restaurants::Hyderabad  ← manually evict
```

